    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Updated idea from discussion with @snario:\r\n* Git should version control a .diff file (a patch on geth which contains the OVM changes) \r\n* `yarn download-geth` should fetch geth at some specific version and apply the patch\r\n* Whenever there is a new geth version some dependabot will auto create a new pull request with the naive merge strategy\r\n* If it just works, merge it. Otherwise maybe assign someone to deal with the merge conflict\r\n\r\nThis will allow us to always be up-to-date with each geth version, instead of having to manually rebase.",
