    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Going to close this for two reasons:\r\n1. It's not too hard to diff with upstream Geth, simply `git diff ./go-ethereum ./optimism/l2geth`. I do this quite frequently when looking for ways to reduce the diff.\r\n2. As part of Bedrock, we're going to be moving away from `l2geth` in the monorepo in favor of having geth in a separate repository, mainly for the purpose of maintaining history more easily. This will effectively fix the issue.",
